        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/4491bb/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-06-24T00:56:19.413Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I‚Äôd like to be able to add alt text to GIFs, images, videos and link thumbnails/previews.</p>\n<p>I am in a chat group on WhatsApp currently and there is a person who is visually impaired. Sometimes a joke gets made using a GIF, and it would be nice to add the alt text in a way that that user can access it but it doesn‚Äôt have to be implemented via some work around such as a caption or another message, such that if a person forgets to add an alt text they can go back to the message and add it later.</p>\n<p>Being able to add the alt text during upload and also being able to modify a message if it was forgotten would be very important, because accessibility is a thing people are likely to forget, so it should be amendable.</p>\n<p>I don‚Äôt want to use a workaround like sending a second message after or adding text somewhere in the message explaining the image. Those make it cumbersome to use for both the writer and the reader, because a reader would then have to find the right message and listen to the entire text if it contains more than just the caption. Native support would be ideal.</p>",
