        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/zetabeta/{size}/54310_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-11T15:12:58.269Z",
        "cooked": "<p>i don‚Äôt think operating system supports this.</p>\n<p>there is file-in metadata, ‚Äúcomment‚Äù section can contain text data. do accessibility readers support reading ‚Äúcomment‚Äù field. ‚Äúcomment‚Äù field is not directly intended for describing picture.</p>\n<p>but fixing image file‚Äôs ‚Äúcomment‚Äù field is not trivial action.</p>\n<p>mastodon has alt-text feature, which is built-in in mastodon system. having a alt-text feature within a communication system has some advantages, like fixing alt-text afterwards without altering image file.</p>\n<p>possibly i report more later.</p>",
