        "created_at": "2026-01-11T19:47:30.936Z",
        "cooked": "<p>i put this picture, which has ‚Äúcomment‚Äù field filled with something. my guess is, that few text readers can read it.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/3/13eab51c849c4b9db809fea125cef70960fffd6d.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/13eab51c849c4b9db809fea125cef70960fffd6d\" title=\"accessibilitytest\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/3/13eab51c849c4b9db809fea125cef70960fffd6d.jpeg\" alt=\"accessibilitytest\" data-base62-sha1=\"2QbVGkiDooNCT9Qsb0t8sBStupf\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">accessibilitytest</span><span class=\"informations\">200√ó200 13 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div> (you can use picture freely, btw.)</p>\n<p>i‚Äôm little bit multi-minded should there be alt-text support or not. should it be in pictures or messaging system. implementing alt-text afterwards is little bit problematic.</p>\n<p>this is a good time to remind. that metadata in files may also contain location data. sometimes knows as exif data. users should be aware of this.</p>\n<p>edit: picture is pointless. this forum removes all metadata and exif data, including ‚Äúcomment‚Äù.</p>",
